lass=title> Re: First SERIOUS story</span><hr size=1> I apologise sincerely. <br>
<br>
I mis-read the cut to the barn.  Guess I should have reread the story again before I posted. Classic application of do what I say, not what I do. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If anything lengthen the description of the city and then cut to the barn, it may add a nice contrast.  <br>
<br>
Of course you should keep the first line if you like it but I would drop that &quot;obtrusively&quot;.<br>
<br>
I recommend you get, or borrow from the library, a copy of Stephen King's On Writing which is brilliant book on the craft of storytelling. <br>
<br>
Oh and if you want another tip, always try to practice good writing. I think half the arguments on forums and newsgroups wouldn't happen if people could convey their thoughts correctly into the written word. And anyway practice makes perfect. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
